features.name: DUF905 Bacterial protein of unknown function (DUF905)
SSB Plays an important role in DNA replication, recombination and repair. Binds to ssDNA and to an array of partner proteins to recruit them to their sites of action during DNA metabolism
PIN Toxic component of a toxin-antitoxin (TA) module. An RNase
CMD Antioxidant protein with alkyl hydroperoxidase activity. Required for the reduction of the AhpC active site cysteine residues and for the regeneration of the AhpC enzyme activity
